Mets Value Team at About $1.3 Billion, New York Post Reports

-- B y   J a m e s   K r a u s
-- 
2011-03-10T05:44:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-10/mets-value-team-at-about-1-3-billion-new-york-post-reports.html
The  New York Mets  expect to raise
$200 million selling a 25 percent stake in the baseball team,
valuing the franchise at about $1.3 billion, the New York Post
reported, citing unidentified person.  The valuation includes $500 million in debt, the newspaper
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Kraus at 
 jkraus2@bloomberg.net  